<DOC><DOCNO> AP880829-0106 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-29-88 1241EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--BridgeCollapse     08-29 0124</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Bridge Collapse,0127</SECOND><HEAD>13 Injured in Bridge Collapse in Nepal</HEAD><DATELINE>KATMANDU, Nepal (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A wooden bridge collapsed Monday asBhuddist pilgrims were crossing it and 13 people were injured,authorities said.   Witnesses said about 20 people were on the 500-yard-longpedestrian bridge over the Bagmati River at the time of theaccident.   The devotees were going to Patan from Katmandu to a Buddhistfestival in the ancient city situated south of the Nepalese capital.   Two of the injured were hospitalized in critical condition.   The 66-year-old bridge was one of the three spans linking thecities of Katmandu and Patan. Although authorities banned vehiculartraffic from the bridge after a truck fell off it five years ago,it was heavily traveled by pedestrians.</TEXT></DOC>